The paper deals with algorithms for solving connectivity problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of algorithms and computational complexity. The use of tree decomposition and treewidth is a common technique in the design of algorithms for graphs, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions linear algebra techniques, which could place it in categories such as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper deals with counting and weighted versions of the problems, which could suggest a category such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
